      <abstract>The Monroe Street Church in Chicago's East Garfield Park neighborhood may have been
        gathered in 1911 with and the church's first minister was likely Rev. Francis Little Hayes.
        In 1918, the Monroe Street Church and California Avenue Church federated to form the Monroe
        Street Federated Church. The church dissolved in 1933. This collection includes membership
        records, baptismal records, marriage records, yearbook reports, and some financial
        records.</abstract>
