    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Monroe Street Church in Chicago's East Garfield Park neighborhood may have been
        gathered in 1911 based on the records available. The first minister listed in the records
        for the church was Rev. Francis Little Hayes. The denominational affiliation of the church
        is unclear; Rev. Hayes maintained fellowship with the Congregationalists and Baptists and
        the church is not listed in the Congregational Yearbook. Rev. Hayes's obituary in the 1926
        Congregational Year Book suggests the California Avenue Church become the Monroe Street
        Church in 1911, however, this contradicts other sources. In 1918, the Monroe Street Church
        and California Avenue Church federated to form the Monroe Street Federated Church. The
        church dissolved in 1933.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection of records for the Monroe Street Federated Church primarily contains vital
        membership records. This collection includes membership records, baptismal records, marriage
        records, listings of church ministers and officers, yearbook reports, and some financial
        records.</p>
    </scopecontent>
